gather()

Use gather to turn ‘gap_wide’ into a long format dataset Key and value. One column is the key and the other will be the value :: - telling R to use a package for a single function

gap_long <- gap_wide %>% 
  gather(key=obstype_year, value=obs_values)

head(gap_long)
## # A tibble: 6 x 2
##   obstype_year obs_values

gap_long <- gap_wide %>% 
  gather(key=obstype_year, value=obs_values, 
         dplyr:: starts_with("pop"),

Keep columns with ‘-’ in gather()

gap_long <- gap_wide %>% 
  gather(key=obstype_year,
         value=obs_values, 
  -continent, -country)
head(gap_long)
## # A tibble: 6 x 4

separate out the year

gap_long <- gap_wide %>% 
  gather(key=obstype_year,
         value=obs_values, 
  -continent, -country) %>% 
  separate(obstype_year,
           into=c("obs_type", "year"), sep="_",
           convert=T)

##convert=T turns year from a character into an integer

head(gap_long)
## # A tibble: 6 x 5
##   continent      country  obs_type  year obs_values

Plot long format data

life_df <- gap_long %>% 
  filter(obs_type=="lifeExp",
         continent=="Americas")

ggplot(data=life_df, aes(x=year, y=obs_values, color=country)) + geom_line()

Using gap_long, calculate and plot the the mean life expectancy for each continent over time from 1982 to 2007. Give your plot a title and assign x and y labels. Hint: use the dplyr::group_by() and dplyr::summarize() functions.

life_df <- gap_long %>% 
  filter(obs_type=="lifeExp") %>% 
  filter(year %in% c(1982:2007))

head(life_df)
## # A tibble: 6 x 5
##   continent      country obs_type  year obs_values
##       <chr>        <chr>    <chr> <int>      <dbl>
## 1    Africa      Algeria  lifeExp  1982     61.368
## 2    Africa       Angola  lifeExp  1982     39.942
## 3    Africa        Benin  lifeExp  1982     50.904
## 4    Africa     Botswana  lifeExp  1982     61.484
## 5    Africa Burkina Faso  lifeExp  1982     48.122
## 6    Africa      Burundi  lifeExp  1982     47.471
tail(life_df)
## # A tibble: 6 x 5
##   continent        country obs_type  year obs_values
##       <chr>          <chr>    <chr> <int>      <dbl>
## 1    Europe         Sweden  lifeExp  2007     80.884
## 2    Europe    Switzerland  lifeExp  2007     81.701
## 3    Europe         Turkey  lifeExp  2007     71.777
## 4    Europe United Kingdom  lifeExp  2007     79.425
## 5   Oceania      Australia  lifeExp  2007     81.235
## 6   Oceania    New Zealand  lifeExp  2007     80.204
group_example=life_df %>% 
  dplyr:: group_by(continent, year) %>% 
  dplyr:: summarize(mean=mean(obs_values)) 
  

ggplot(data=group_example, aes(x=year, y=mean, color=continent)) + geom_line() + theme_bw()

spread()

Getting the dataset back into the wide format to look like original gapminder

gap_normal <-  gap_long %>% 
  spread(key=obs_type, value=obs_values)
